ivorce: Evidence triple talaq only counts as one divorce","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 6, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Yazid ibn Rukanah reported: Rukanah had divorced his wife irrevocably and the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, only counted it as one divorce. Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 2196 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to Al-Albani Ibn al-Qayyim writes, \"It was judged to count as one divorce by Al-Zubayr ibn\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":6217,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/11\/most-beloved-sahabah-prophet\/","url_meta":{"origin":7912,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Sahaba: Most beloved companions to the Prophet","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 11, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"'Amr ibn al-'As reported: I said, \u201cWhich person is most beloved to you?\u201d The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cAisha.\u201d I said, \u201cI mean among men.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cHer father.\u201d I said, \u201cThen who?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cUmar ibn al-Khattab,\u201d and the Prophet mentioned other men.\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/7912","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"hre